\cf2 An event is logged only if it is verifiable, reflects a concrete action or institutional change, and has plausible democratic relevance beyond rhetoric. Statements alone are included only when accompanied by formal authority or institutional consequence.\
Each qualifying event is assessed for direction (erosive or restorative), scope (localized or systemic), and durability (temporary or precedent-setting). Events are evaluated independently and aggregated to determine net movement. There are no preset movement targets and no narrative smoothing. When events warrant significant movement, the clock reflects it.\
All movements are traceable to logged events. Methodology is applied consistently over time, and any recalibration is documented transparently.\
